snippet.textDisplay:
What was that at 3:35 - 3:36?  Is this really the level of a professional singer—let alone something uploaded and produced by Coke Studio? How could a performance like this be released on such a reputed platform?

It’s exactly because of songs like this that people say Coke Studio India’s standards have dropped, or that they can’t be compared with the rest. Why did Sarthak even contribute here? If he truly wanted to, he could have sung the entire song himself—and I’m certain that would have at least salvaged it.

And to those praising this underwhelming track—please go back and listen to the older songs of Coke Studio India by Amit Trivedi, A.R. Rahman, Ram Sampath, Vishal Dadlani, Salim–Sulaiman, Sachin–Jigar, and others. Those were true performances in every sense: music, production, lyrics, and above all, STANDARDS.
